description:
Saving the Wild - Part 1: The Big Cats | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'Saving the Wild - Part 2' here: https://youtu.be/rYvCo6kTLxE

Across game reserves in Southern Africa, conservationists are attaching tracking collars to lions and cheetahs. The data collected is essential for wildlife conservation, however attaching them isnt straightforward. This episode follows the complications of the procedure and reveals why theyre so essential to conservation. They locate a cheetah thats trapped in a poachers snare. The unsuspecting cheetah has walked right through the hidden barbed wire snare, trapping its body in the noose. The snare has sliced through his abdomen. It's a severe injury and if hes to stand any chance of survival he must undergo immediate surgery. A mobile vet clinic is set up, and a team of experts and volunteers have raced in to help. 

Meanwhile in Dinokeng, management has been alerted that a pride of lions has breached the perimeter. After heavy rains, a flood gate was damaged, leaving a gap just big enough for the curious lions to get through. Now on the loose, they freely explore the bushland surrounding the reserve, roaming dangerously close to civilization.  Dinokengs management are on a crucial mission to return them to the reserve. However, its not going to be easy to safely relocate the entire pride.
